definitions.definition: To throw with a sudden effort or thrust; to hurl or launch .
To send forth suddenly or rapidly; to emit ; to shoot.
examples: As the sun dart ed forth his beams, she dart ed a meaningful glance at me.

definitions.definition: To shoot with a dart, especially a tranquilizer dart .
examples: They had to dart the animal to get close enough to help

definitions.definition: To fly or pass swiftly, like a dart; to move rapidly in one direction; to shoot out quickly.
To start and run with speed; to shoot rapidly along.
examples: The deer darted from the thicket.
The fish darted under a stone.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To throw with a sudden effort or thrust; to hurl or launch .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To send forth suddenly or rapidly; to emit ; to shoot.
( transitive ) To shoot with a dart, especially a tranquilizer dart .
( intransitive ) To fly or pass swiftly, like a dart; to move rapidly in one direction; to shoot out quickly.
( intransitive ) To start and run with speed; to shoot rapidly along.
